arXiv:2411.11463v2 Announce Type: replace Abstract: We suggest a new generalization of the $\mathrm{U}(n)$ Yang-Mills theory obtained by relaxing the condition of covariant constancy of the Hermitian form in the fibers, $
abla_a g_{\alpha eta'} 
e 0$. This theory is a simpler analogue of the metric-affine gravity with $
abla_a g_{bc} 
e 0$. In our case, connection $
abla_a$ and Hermitian form $g_{\alpha eta'}$ are two independent variables so total curvature and total potential are no longer anti-Hermitian matrices: thus, along with the standard YM potential $ oldsymbol{A}_a$ and field strength tensor $ oldsymbol{F}_{ab}$, it contains non-trivially interacting fields $ oldsymbol{B}_a$, $ oldsymbol{h}$, and $ oldsymbol{G}_{ab}$, $ oldsymbol{N}_a$, forming a non-Abelian generalization of St"{u}ckelberg theory. Due to the spontaneous symmetry breaking $\mathrm{GL}(n,\mathbb{C}) 	o \mathrm{U}(n)$, these new fields can be made massive, and the limit $M	o\infty$ restores the standard YM theory.
